            "title": "Canada's Gran Tierra Energy secures new $75 million credit facility",
            "description": "<html><body><ul>\n<li>Gran Tierra Energy (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NYSE:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/GTE\" title=\"Gran Tierra Energy Inc.\">GTE</a></span>), through its wholly owned subsidiary, Gran Tierra Energy Colombia GmbH, a Swiss limited liability company, entered into a reserve-based lending facility with commitments of up to $75 million.</li>\n<li>The new <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/pr/20069975-gran-tierra-energy-inc-announces-new-us-75-million-credit-facility\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"facility\">facility</a> has a final maturity date in 36 months from the closing date.</li>\n<li>Interest payable on the facility is based on a Term Secured Overnight Financing Rate plus a margin of 4.50% per annum.</li>\n<li>All outstanding principal, interest, and other payment obligations are due on the maturity date with option to prepay without prepayment penalty.</li>\n</ul>\n</body></html>",
