            "id": "4431978",
            "title": "ABB reports mixed Q1 results; initiates Q1 and FY25 outlook",
            "description": "<html><body><ul>\n<li>ABB <a href=\"https://search.abb.com/library/Download.aspx?DocumentID=9AKK108471A0338&amp;LanguageCode=en&amp;DocumentPartId=&amp;Action=Launch&amp;_gl=1*1k1whrn*_gcl_au*MjA2NDI1NzEzMC4xNzQ0ODc2Njc5*_ga*MTkyMDE0MzgxNS4xNzQ0ODc2Njgw*_ga_46ZFBRSZNM*MTc0NDg3NjY3OS4xLjAuMTc0NDg3NjY3OS42MC4wLjA.\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">press release</a>  (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/ABBNY\" title=\"ABB Ltd\">OTCPK:ABBNY</a>): Q1  GAAP EPS of $0.60 <font color=\"green\"> beats by $0.07</font>.</li>\n<li>Revenue of $7.93B (+0.8% Y/Y) <font color=\"red\"> misses by $260M</font>.</li>\n<li>Orders $9,213 million, +3%; comparable +5%.</li>\n<li>Operational EBITA $1,597 million; margin 20.2%.</li>\n<li>Cash flow from operating activities $684 million; -6%.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Outlook: In full-year 2025</strong>, we expect a positive book-to-bill, comparable revenue growth in the mid-single digit range and the Operational EBITA margin to improve year-on-year, however acknowledging the increased uncertainty for the global business environment.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>In the second quarter of 2025</strong>, we anticipate comparable revenue growth in the mid-single digit range, and the Operational EBITA margin to remain broadly stable with last year’s 19.0%; however, acknowledging the increased uncertainty for the global business environment. We expect improved business results in 2025 to offset the year-on-year headwind from favorable net non-repeats of 30 basis points in Corporate &amp; Other in the second quarter of 2024.</li>\n</ul>\n</body></html>",
